Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Gochujang Beef Udon Noodles in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Trim the @green beans{80%grams}, then cut into thirds.

Trim the @pak choi{1%unit}, then separate the leaves. Cut any large leaves in half lengthways down the middle.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%grams} and green beans. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Use a #spoon{} to break the mince up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, crush the @salted peanuts{25%grams} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the pak choi and garlic. Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @gochujang paste{50%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @soy sauce{15%ml}, @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{50%ml} to the pan.

> See pantry for soy sauce and water amounts.

Stir to combine, bring to the boil and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @udon noodles{220%grams} to the pan.

Toss to coat, using a #fork{} to gently separate them. Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Share the gochujang beef noodles between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the crushed peanuts to finish.

Enjoy!